{
  "stem": "26111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, with pleasure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the, the thing it gave me was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a kind of-- I guess the current-- currently fashionable word is 'self-esteem.' That isn't quite right because I, I never had any lacking self-esteem.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it made my esteem clearer to myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You esteem yourself as what?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As what you are.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And since I didn't quite know what I was, since I was surrounded by all these several, and, and often contradictory, facets, such as religious, who are you religiously; who are you as a national; who are you in-- as a-- as a-- as a-- as a-- at this stage in your life, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this, and especially the Jewish identity, had been kind of nebulous, due to the very unreligious attitude and-- I wouldn't say un-Jewish attitude.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My parents were always [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] conscious of being Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They just didn't do anything about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were [BACKGROUND NOISE] unreligious or areligious by-- through intellectual reasoning, which really made it very hard for them to have a faith.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they didn't-- were not able to somehow link the sense of Jewishness that they did have with the religious-- with the religious sense of Jewish religion that they did not have.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a conflict there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was kind of caught in-between, admiring as I did the, the qualities of both my, my parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I respected the, the areligiousness, non-religiousness.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It wasn't anti-religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just for them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't tell anybody else what to do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They felt that way.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I didn't necessarily say that I would follow it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I respected somewhat less the degree of their assimilation into German life because-- somewhat less.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
